This paper is about improving the performance of artificial neural networks using feedback, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. The use of transfer entropy as a measure for the relevance of certain pathways in the network suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of feedback in neural networks is also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the mention of a standard benchmark task suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
